\begin_layout Standard
ABSTRACT::: Ly 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 photons emitted from the first stars formed inside the galaxies or halos
 in the early universe.
 Ly 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 photons can be scattered through the intergalactic medium, and can be observed
 as Ly 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 emitting sources.
 We examine the Ly 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 line transfer mechanism by tracing scattering histories of Ly 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 photons in the intergalactic medium of the early universe.
 We build the 3D Monte Carlo simulation of Ly 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 scattering, which can be applied to the any cell based reionization cosmology
 simulation data.
 The simulation is tested with various geometry having analytical models
 first.
 Then we test the code in the density field of the intergalactic medium
 generated by cosmological reionized simulation.
 The emergent line profile from the simulation could give constraints to
 the Lyman 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 emitting mechanism and the reionization history.
 
