\end_inset

 can be Lorentz transformed to the atom rest frame frequency 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu'$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\nu'=\nu\left(1-\frac{\mathbf{v}\centerdot\hat{n}}{c}\right).\label{eq:LT}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}$
\end_inset

 is the velocity vector of the atom, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{n}$
\end_inset

 is the photon's direction vector.
 Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:LT"

\end_inset

 is valid for non-relativistic atom 
\begin_inset Formula $v\ll c$
\end_inset

 .
 The second order term of 
\begin_inset Formula $v/c$
\end_inset

 can be ignored.
 Put Equation 
